CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 5, 1955, pg. 8A, reads: "First Session - After his installation Tuesday morning, new County Commissioner Howard B. Stewart (right) assumed to rostrum with Commissioner John M. Walker (left) and John J. Kane to get down to business by opening biddings for Thanksgiving Day dinners for county employes [employees]. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Allegheny County Commissioners John M. Walker, John J. Kane, and Howard B. Stewart, posed in office with photographs on wall and VFW certificate inscribed to Kane
